org.nerd4j.csv.writer

Interface CSVWriter<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - type of the data model representing the CSV record.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, Flushable

    public interface CSVWriter<M>
extends Closeable, Flushable
    Represents a CSV destination writer.

    Reads an object of type M that represents the data model and writes the corresponding CSV record to the given destination.

    Synchronization

    CSV writers are not synchronized. It is recommended to create separate CSV writer instances for each thread. If multiple threads access a CSV writer concurrently, it must be synchronized externally.

    Since version 1.2.0

    support has been added for the new Java 8 Stream API. Now it's possible to use the CSVWriter in a functional way to drain a sequence of elements i.e.

    • Iterator
    • Spliterator
    • Stream
    For example can be used to drain a Stream writing all elements in a CSV destination in this way:
    writer.drain(stream).intoCSV();
    or in this way:
    writer.drain(stream).forEach( write -> do something ).intoCSV();
    Author:
    Nerd4J Team

    • Method Detail

      • writeModel

        void writeModel(M model)
         throws IOException,
                ModelToCSVBindingException,
                CSVProcessException
        Writes the given data model, formatted like a CSV record into the configured CSV destination.

        This method has a cleaner interface but handles processing errors by throwing CSVProcessException therefore it may be slow. If performance matters use write(Object) instead.

        Parameters:
        model - the data model to write.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs reading the CSV source.
        ModelToCSVBindingException - if an error occurs during model binding.
        CSVProcessException - if an error occurs during data processing.

      • write

        CSVProcessOutcome<M> write(M model)
                    throws IOException,
                           ModelToCSVBindingException
        Writes the given data model, formatted like a CSV record into the configured CSV destination.

        IMPORTANT for performance reasons there is only one instance of the read outcome. So the internal values of this object may vary during execution.

        Parameters:
        model - the data model to write.
        Returns:
        the outcome of the writing process.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs reading the CSV source.
        ModelToCSVBindingException - if an error occurs during model binding.

      • drain

        default org.nerd4j.csv.writer.CSVStreamDrainer<M> drain(Stream<M> stream)
        Drains the given Stream writing all elements into the CSV destination.

        This method is intended to be used in a functional way like:
        writer.drain(stream).intoCSV();
        or
        writer.drain(stream).forEach( write -> do something ).intoCSV();

        Parameters:
        stream - Stream to be drained.
        Returns:
        the class able to drain the Stream.
        Since:
        1.2.0
